<div id="review_2395989856" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2395989856" />
    <a title="Hannah Green" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/45502925-hannah-green"><img alt="Hannah Green" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1468022289p2/45502925.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2395989856?book_show_action=true">May 22, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Hannah Green" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Hannah Green" href="/user/show/45502925-hannah-green">Hannah Green</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2395989856" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3535987631674720072">I wanted to give this book 2.5 stars but that&apos;s obviously impossible. The first two chapters are EXCRUCIATING. I understand that the author was trying to remind us that the narrator is a seventh grader, but the tone is so juvenile you&apos;d think she was a first grader. Or Stephanie Meyer. I powered through because of the many glowing Goodreads reviews and it wasn&apos;t not worth it? I&apos;d say this book gets the student musician experience about half right. The feelings are VERY real, as is being motivate</span>
  <span id="freeText3535987631674720072" style="display:none">I wanted to give this book 2.5 stars but that's obviously impossible. The first two chapters are EXCRUCIATING. I understand that the author was trying to remind us that the narrator is a seventh grader, but the tone is so juvenile you'd think she was a first grader. Or Stephanie Meyer. I powered through because of the many glowing Goodreads reviews and it wasn't not worth it? I'd say this book gets the student musician experience about half right. The feelings are VERY real, as is being motivated by handsome famous musicians (hello, first twenty years of my life), but TBH if there were six finalists in an under-21 competition, at least three of them would have been Steve Landauers.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3535987631674720072" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


